# Google Sheets API Configuration
# Get your API key from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# Note: Use NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix for client-side environment variables
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key_here

# Your Google Spreadsheet ID
# Found in the URL: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/[SPREADSHEET_ID]/edit
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SHEET_ID=your_spreadsheet_id_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Create a Google Cloud Project: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Enable Google Sheets API
# 3. Create API credentials (API Key with restrictions to Sheets API only)
# 4. Restrict the API key to:
#    - HTTP referrers (preserve.ml, preserve-ml.github.io)
#    - Google Sheets API only
# 5. Create a Google Sheet with columns: Timestamp, Name, Email, Company
# 6. Make the sheet publicly editable (or set proper permissions)
# 7. Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values
